<meta name="description" content="In the manufacture of saws, the straightening forms a large proportion of the manipulative processes. The cutting of the teeth, the grinding, the polishing, the tempering, and the finishing: each of these processes is accompanied by a straightening operation; for in insuring an equal amount of tension at an parts of the blade lies one of the principal elements necessary to the production of a good saw, and a blade can hardly have any mechanical operation performed upon it without affecting its tension and straightness.">

